                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d352">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/6497: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal (<persName type="from"
                            >Fish</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-26T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 26, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 26—3:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1101. From Murphy. I received last evening Department’s 256, August 19, 9 p.m. to
                    Casablanca regarding British desire to enjoy publicity in French North Africa
                    concerning British participation in the American supply program for that
                    area.</p>
                <p>Much would depend, it seems to me, on the nature of the publicity campaign
                    undertaken. It is suggested that the British be requested to submit for the
                    Department’s consideration an outline of whatever program they wish to undertake
                    in order that study might be given the matter to insure that the British program
                    does not conflict <pb facs="0371" n="365" xml:id="pg_365"/> with whatever
                    American publicity the Department may contemplate. I should be grateful for an
                    opportunity to discuss this question after arrival in Washington which should be
                    approximately August 29. [Murphy.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
